{
  "texts": [
    "The K parameters are also learned during auto-encoder training.",
    "The background noise is added to the mixed speech components to generate the final speech spectrogram.",
    "To summarize, our speech synthesizer has the following learnable parameters: the M = 80 prototype filter parameters for each of the N = 6 formant filters and the broadband filters (totalling M(N + 1) = 560), the three parameters f θ, a and b 0 relating the centre frequency and bandwidth for the formant filters (totalling 18), and K parameters for the background noise (256 for female and 512 for male).",
    "The total number of parameters for female speakers is 834, and that for male speakers is 1,090.",
    "Note that these parameters are speaker-dependent but time-independent, and they can be learned together with the speech encoder during the training of the speech-to-speech auto-encoder, using the speaker's speech only."
  ]
}